article.headline: Florida A&M 76, Norfolk State 64
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Tony Tate scored 26 points, including nine points in a critical stretch of the second half, to lead Florida A&M to a 76-64 win over Norfolk State on Wednesday night. Florida A&M (5-8, 1-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) took a 61-60 lead on a Glen Elliott layup with 6:59 left in the game after trailing by as much as four earlier in the second half. After two free throws by Joe Ballard made it 63-60, Tate scored nine points in a 13-4 run over the final 5:22 to secure the win for the Rattlers. Rome Sanders added 16 and six rebounds points for Florida A&M, which shot 58.1 percent from the field in the game. Tony Murphy scored 19 points and Larry Vickers added 14 points and six offensive rebounds as the only scorers in double figures for Norfolk State (2-10, 1-1). The Rattlers capitalized on turnovers, scoring 28 points off 17 Spartans giveaways. Florida A&M also held a 22-6 advantage at the foul line.
